    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "When I move my shada file to a different location and have ~/.local/share/nvim/shada/main.shada be a symlink to that location, neovim overwrites the symlink with a file. It should respect symlinks and update the file referred to by the symlink rather than overwriting the symlink itself.",
    "closed_at": "2018-09-04T22:41:06Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Duplicate of #1674\r\n\r\n> Vim intentionally doesn't follow symlinks for .viminfo, because that can\r\nbe used for a symlink attack, a security issue.\r\n\r\nYou can work around this by simply setting the \"n\" flag of 'shada' option.",
